Zoey Belle is 13 today and I’m not OK. Who said you can be a teenager?! 🥹😭

Happy Birthday to my favorite. Auntie loves you always. 💕
Summer Lovin’ 💋

I’m painting my favorite photos that I’ve taken over the years.. inspired by my @picsbyniesey account. I call this one “Cranes in the Sky”. 😊

I’d tell you that I found a new hobby recently… but the truth is that I used to draw a lot as a child and teen. As an adult I forgot how much I enjoyed it but I’m grateful that I’ve been able to rediscover this creative side of myself during this quiet and unprecedented time in my business. Forgot how much I enjoy sitting still for hours solely focused on little details.

So here’s a gentle reminder to be still. Stay creative. Explore new parts of yourself. You may just find something that’s always been a part of you and is ready to resurface. 💛

Happy Birthday to my beautiful, kind, big hearted, smart, talented, hilarious, ballplayer/producer/actress/sommelier fiancée @laurenwilkinssss! How did I get this lucky?! 🥰

Love you forever and always and I thank heaven and earth for all your Virgo ways. 😂

“Black Beverly Hills”

Finished my second painting this week. Took me about six weeks to complete since work slowly started creeping back into my days after the WGA strike ended. This one was more challenging but I am so proud of the finished result!

I sketched and painted this based on a photo I took two years ago of @jasonrembert crossing Slauson Ave after the Insecure season 5 block party in View Park. 

I love everything about the details captured in this moment, but most especially I love the symbolism of light and dark portrayed in the shadows and attributes throughout. MLK once said, “darkness cannot drive out darkness; only light can do that”. May we all find light even in our darkest days. 💛

Michael Benjamin Latt. 

Our sweet, dear, beloved comrade Michael. We love you and you loved us back so deeply. It’s hard to process such an unfathomable tragedy when the person carried so much light and added so much beauty to our world. He was all about community, love, and uplifting and connecting others. I’ve never met a more kind and compassionate humanitarian like him and can honestly say I may never again. That’s how special his friendship and support was to me and all of us who feel honored to have known him. 

We will continue your work and legacy. 
We will never forget you. 
We will forever be impacted by you. 
We will always love you.

These are about all the words that I can even remotely begin to put together as I continue to grapple with this deep loss. That said, the best thing I can think of was to share Michael’s own story with the world via his VoyageLA article from a few years ago. May his words and the way he lived inspire us all.

“We all deserve love, compassion and kindness from ourselves and others.” 
— Michael Latt
